<subSubSection id="41F76577FFB1FFD4C29CC37CE266F603" pageId="7" pageNumber="8" type="discussion">
<paragraph id="095236FCFFB1FFD4C29CC37CE266F603" blockId="7.[151,1437,1625,1831]" pageId="7" pageNumber="8">
<emphasis id="3B99EAEEFFB1FFD4C29CC37CE746F7B3" bold="true" box="[199,308,1661,1687]" pageId="7" pageNumber="8">Remarks</emphasis>
. 
<bibRefCitation id="6D7C4B0DFFB1FFD4C31AC37CE46CF7BC" author="Linsenmaier, W." box="[321,542,1661,1688]" pageId="7" pageNumber="8" pagination="1 - 144" refId="ref23614" refString="Linsenmaier, W. (1968) Revision der Familie Chrysididae (Hymenoptera). Zweiter Nachtrag. Mitteilungen der Schweizerischen Entomologischen Gesellschaft, 41 (1 - 4), 1 - 144." type="journal article" year="1968">Linsenmaier (1968)</bibRefCitation>
reported that 
<specimenCount id="1FEBFD75FFB1FFD4C0E2C37CE48EF7B3" box="[697,764,1661,1687]" pageId="7" pageNumber="8" type="female">one ♀</specimenCount>
from 
<collectingCountry id="71FA766CFFB1FFD4C11BC37CE5D0F7B3" box="[832,930,1661,1687]" name="Lebanon" pageId="7" pageNumber="8">Lebanon</collectingCountry>
has coarse punctation on the posterior part of the metasoma, although less coarse than 
<taxonomicName id="CEED4D7FFFB1FFD4C03FC3A0E27CF79F" authority="(Mocsary, 1889)" baseAuthorityName="Mocsary" baseAuthorityYear="1889" box="[612,1038,1697,1723]" class="Insecta" family="Chrysididae" genus="Holopyga" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="7" pageNumber="8" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="caucasica">
<emphasis id="3B99EAEEFFB1FFD4C03FC3A0E538F79F" box="[612,842,1697,1723]" italics="true" pageId="7" pageNumber="8">Holopyga caucasica</emphasis>
(
<bibRefCitation id="6D7C4B0DFFB1FFD4C102C3A0E274F79F" author="Mocsary, A." box="[857,1030,1697,1723]" pageId="7" pageNumber="8" refId="ref24067" refString="Mocsary, A. (1889) Monographia Chrysididarum Orbis Terrarum Universi. Hungarian Academy of Science, Budapest, 643 pp." type="book" year="1889">Mocsáry, 1889</bibRefCitation>
)
</taxonomicName>
. This specimen is no longer deposited in his collection, however, it could be 
<taxonomicName id="CEED4D7FFFB1FFD4C027C3C7E562F7FB" baseAuthorityName="Mocsary" baseAuthorityYear="1889" box="[636,784,1734,1759]" class="Insecta" family="Chrysididae" genus="Holopyga" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="7" pageNumber="8" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="caucasica">
<emphasis id="3B99EAEEFFB1FFD4C027C3C7E562F7FB" box="[636,784,1734,1759]" italics="true" pageId="7" pageNumber="8">H. caucasica</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
. In fact, Linsenmaier, based on the examination of specimens deposited in his collection, considered as 
<taxonomicName id="CEED4D7FFFB1FFD4C0F0C3EBE54CF627" baseAuthorityName="Mocsary" baseAuthorityYear="1889" box="[683,830,1770,1795]" class="Insecta" family="Chrysididae" genus="Holopyga" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="7" pageNumber="8" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="caucasica">
<emphasis id="3B99EAEEFFB1FFD4C0F0C3EBE54CF627" box="[683,830,1770,1795]" italics="true" pageId="7" pageNumber="8">H. caucasica</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
a species from 
<collectingCountry id="71FA766CFFB1FFD4C1B6C3E8E24CF627" box="[1005,1086,1769,1795]" name="Cyprus" pageId="7" pageNumber="8">Cyprus</collectingCountry>
not yet described, with coarser punctation on the second metasomal tergum. This species group needs revision.
</paragraph>
